description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An opportunity has arisen within Homerton University Hospital, for a highly skilled, knowledgeable, dynamic and innovative Endoscopy Senior Charge Nurse to professionally and managerially lead and manage the Unit and its team, in this exciting service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for someone with commitment to Endoscopy and Gastroenterology with a proven track record of experience and achievement in their current role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be accountable for implementing, driving and monitoring the quality and safety agenda and monitor standards within the clinical area of the Homerton Endoscopy Unit, as well as operationally managing the service on a day to day basis.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You should have excellent communication skills and be able to work and manage a large team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You should also be flexible and approachable with a positive attitude, as this is the ethos of the unit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The unit also houses an externally managed decontamination unit service within the Endoscopy Unit itself; it would be an advantage to have a working knowledge of decontamination.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will represent the service at clinical and operational groups and committees, within the Trust, and have excellent abilities to present to all hierarchy’s of the Trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For this role we are looking for a flexible, proactive, reliable and experienced endoscopy nurse, who can work as part of a large multidisciplinary team and on an individual basis with colleagues. Comprehensive management experience is essential for this post.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In return we will offer you a comprehensive induction, with ongoing learning and development opportunities, an annual personal development plan and on the job training with regular supervision from the Divisional Matron of Acute Services, to support your career pathway.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post is offered as a full time position 37.5 hours per week&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jennie Wood,Matron Acute Adult Services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;email jennie.wood@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone on 0208 510 5324&lt;/p&gt;
